company.tagline: The most realistic voice AI platform
company.description: ElevenLabs is an AI audio research and deployment company. As voice becomes a primary interface for using technology, we build AI that makes these interactions effortless and human. We began with ultra-realistic AI voices - clear, expressive, and multilingual. Today, we advance AI audio across speech, sound effects, and music, and turn that work into products people use every day.

events.title: Partnership with Ukrainian Public Services
events.description: Partnering with the Ministry of Digital Transformation to add voice to core services.

events.title: Voice AI for India Scale
events.description: Marking a year of rapid development from India’s top enterprises, startups, and creators scaling customer engagement and storytelling.

events.title: Voice ID System Launch
events.description: ElevenLabs and AILAS launch a voice ID system to protect actors from AI misuse. Japanese actors and voice actors can now mark their voices as authorized for AI use.

events.title: Introducing Productions
events.description: Productions is our new managed service offering for ordering human-edited content that looks, sounds, and feels natural. Made for creators and media businesses.

events.title: Scaling UK and US Presence
events.description: ElevenLabs is building local talent hubs and infrastructure to deliver real-time AI audio for enterprises globally.

events.title: Expansion into Brazil
events.description: Launching our first campaign in Brazil with iconic AI voice Fábio Porchat.

events.title: Eleven v3 (alpha) Available in API
events.description: Eleven v3 (alpha), the most expressive text to speech model, is now available in the API for developers.

events.title: Eleven Music Available in API
events.description: Eleven Music is the first API for developers trained on licensed data and cleared for broad commercial use.

events.title: Audio in Air Mail Magazine
events.description: We’re adding audio to Air Mail magazine, so readers can follow it anywhere.

events.title: Leadership Change in Hiring Practices
events.description: CEO mentions that non-traditional hiring outside LinkedIn led to finding a researcher working at a call center.
